cenq:contributing-factor.cenq:contributing-factor-description: The existence of a previous external administration event or other serious adverse on the company file is a powerful indicator of increased risk.
The type and frequency of credit enquiries can impact risk. Typically, companies that are higher risk request various types of credit from different sources more often.
The existence of default information on the company file can be a very powerful indicator of risk.
